.TH XltYesNo 3X "" "" "" ""
.ds )H Rick Scott
.ds ]W @PACKAGE@ Version @VERSION@
.SH NAME
\fIXltYesNo\fP \- Convenience function to bring up a YesNo dialog.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.sS
.iS
\&#include <Xlt/Xlt.h>
.sp \n(PDu
Boolean XltYesNo(\fBwidget, question\fI)
.ta .5i 1.5i
.nf
	Widget	\fBwidget\fI;
	String	\fBquestion\fI;
.wH
.fi
.iE
.sE
.SH DESCRIPTION
.fi
\fIXltYesNo\fP 
Spins in a local event loop processing XEvents until user has chosen.
.IP "\fBwidget\fP"
The parent widget.
.PP 
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns user choice.
.SH RELATED INFORMATION
.na
.ad
